  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Oxaliplatin is a platinum analogue that has significant antitumor activity with better
      tolerability than cisplatin. The objective of the study is to evaluate the safety and
      activity of leucovorin and 5-fluorouracil and leucovorin and 5-fluorouracil plus oxaliplatin
      combination chemotherapy given as adjuvant therapy for curatively-resected, node-positive
      esophageal cancer.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
